1
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:21,333
When are you planning to propose
to Celeste?

2
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:24,400
At this point, I think
it's more important for me

3
00:00:24,467 --> 00:00:26,300
to support her in her dreams.

4
00:00:26,367 --> 00:00:28,800
We both know that it will
never be easy for Celeste

5
00:00:28,867 --> 00:00:30,133
to blend in with the family.

6
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:33,233
So if I were you, don't delay
your proposal further.

7
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:34,700
Seal the deal.

8
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:37,100
Happy birthday, Vivian.

9
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:39,100
Do not speak Chinese
if you don't know

10
00:00:39,167 --> 00:00:41,200
how to pronounce it correctly.

11
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:44,033
I've met you several times
before, Celeste,

12
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:46,400
but I don't know you very well.

13
00:00:46,467 --> 00:00:48,300
I could smell from a mile away

14
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:51,067
that you're hiding something,
Celeste.

15
00:00:51,133 --> 00:00:53,333
I don't have any secrets
to hide.

16
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:54,400
Liar.

17
00:00:54,467 --> 00:00:56,400
You should separate from Tonito,
Celeste.

18
00:00:56,467 --> 00:00:59,767
Because even with your absolute
very best,

19
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:03,467
you will still never be good
enough for my brother.

20
00:01:05,167 --> 00:01:08,033
Aurelia, you're making me feel
uncomfortable.

21
00:01:08,133 --> 00:01:11,367
Do you think I'm flirting
with you, Tonito?

22
00:01:11,433 --> 00:01:13,600
- I'm not.
- No offense meant.

23
00:01:13,667 --> 00:01:16,900
We're friends, but we need
to set healthy boundaries.

24
00:01:16,967 --> 00:01:21,533
My brother and Aurelia may have
mutually agreed to part ways.

25
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:24,600
But for as long as I live,
I won't stop

26
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:26,700
until their family will get back
together again.

27
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,400
Love, wait.

28
00:01:36,933 --> 00:01:38,333
I know you will not tell me.

29
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,967
What did Vivian tell you?

30
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:41,267
I just want to go home.

31
00:01:41,367 --> 00:01:44,267
Love, trust me on this.

32
00:01:44,333 --> 00:01:46,867
Men can build
and carve monuments

33
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:49,300
but these will all crumble
in time.

34
00:01:49,367 --> 00:01:52,333
But your legacy
will endure forever.

35
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:57,900
And that love is the reason
why I love right now.

36
00:01:57,967 --> 00:02:00,867
Celeste, will you be
my happily ever after?

37
00:02:00,933 --> 00:02:02,267
Will you marry me?

38
00:02:02,333 --> 00:02:03,000
Of course.

39
00:02:10,233 --> 00:02:12,833
Do you expect me to go back
to the party?

40
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:14,467
After what dad did to us?

41
00:02:15,733 --> 00:02:17,267
Don't you feel insulted?

42
00:02:17,333 --> 00:02:19,567
Your dad and I
are already annulled.

43
00:02:19,633 --> 00:02:21,900
I don't want to give you
false hope

44
00:02:21,967 --> 00:02:25,900
that your Dad and I will get
back together, okay?

45
00:02:25,967 --> 00:02:27,500
You will just hurt more.

46
00:02:27,567 --> 00:02:30,500
The more I will get hurt
if you will not do anything

47
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:32,533
for you and Dad
to get back together.

48
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:34,433
Hello, Sebastian?

49
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:36,400
Hello, Celeste.

50
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:37,733
Why are you calling?

51
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,800
They are going to the provincial
hospital right now.

52
00:02:39,867 --> 00:02:41,133
Father had a heart attack.

53
00:02:43,267 --> 00:02:45,033
You need to come home
here in Sorsogon.

54
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:47,400
What?

55
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:48,400
Sorsogon?

56
00:02:52,467 --> 00:02:53,267
Sebastian...

57
00:02:54,467 --> 00:02:55,933
No. That's impossible.

58
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,867
I cannot go to Sorsogon.

59
00:02:57,933 --> 00:03:01,667
Celeste, please,
this is an emergency.

60
00:03:01,733 --> 00:03:02,967
Father needs you.

61
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:07,867
Celeste, please go home.

62
00:03:07,933 --> 00:03:10,267
Okay, first and foremost,
don't call me manay .

63
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:12,267
And it's not Celes-te,
it's Celeste.

64
00:03:13,433 --> 00:03:15,700
Celeste, is that still
what you're thinking?

65
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:19,867
Celeste, you haven't been home
for eight years.

66
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:22,900
Even now you can't grant
our request?

67
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,267
You know what Sebastian,
I am so busy.

68
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:27,600
I have so much to do here
in Manila.

69
00:03:27,667 --> 00:03:30,567
I cannot possibly go all the way
to Sorsogon.

70
00:03:31,567 --> 00:03:34,233
You can do that,
you and your mother, Adora.

71
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:37,000
You know, here's the thing.

72
00:03:37,067 --> 00:03:38,233
I'll take care of everything.

73
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:41,667
Just send me the bill,
I'll send something there.

74
00:03:41,733 --> 00:03:45,067
Money is not the reason
why I called you, Celeste.

75
00:03:45,133 --> 00:03:48,300
It's you. Father needs you.

76
00:03:48,367 --> 00:03:49,400
This is not the right time
for you

77
00:03:49,467 --> 00:03:51,300
to think of your anger
towards him.

78
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:56,967
Celeste, if something bad
happens to father,

79
00:03:57,067 --> 00:03:58,400
I'll blame you.

80
00:03:59,967 --> 00:04:01,500
You know, Sebastian,
that's unfair.

81
00:04:06,433 --> 00:04:06,833
Hello?

82
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:08,533
Sebas...

83
00:04:35,967 --> 00:04:37,367
And just like that...

84
00:04:37,433 --> 00:04:40,467
one emergency call
and my life turns upside down.

85
00:04:40,533 --> 00:04:43,500
Will they expect me
to go all the way to Sorsogon?

86
00:04:43,567 --> 00:04:47,100
I mean, can they blame me
if I don't want to go there?

87
00:04:48,167 --> 00:04:49,567
Who will I go home to?

88
00:04:49,633 --> 00:04:52,000
My father? The man who broke
my mother's heart?

89
00:04:54,133 --> 00:04:57,700
Love, no family is ever perfect

90
00:04:57,767 --> 00:05:01,233
but in the end,
family is family.

91
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:02,600
The love will always be there.

92
00:05:04,433 --> 00:05:04,867
Admit it,

93
00:05:06,633 --> 00:05:08,667
that's why you're so affected...

94
00:05:08,733 --> 00:05:09,967
it's because you still care
for them.

95
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:12,933
That they still matter to you

96
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,100
even if you keep shunning them
from your life.

97
00:05:18,133 --> 00:05:21,500
Love, you know I rarely ask
anything of you.

98
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,067
Can you do me a favor?

99
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:30,133
Can you please go home
and visit your sick father?

100
00:05:31,667 --> 00:05:34,767
Now, it may be the best decision
you'll make in your life.

101
00:05:39,167 --> 00:05:39,733
Please?

102
00:06:27,233 --> 00:06:30,433
The truth, are you going
to Sorsogon or Paris?

103
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:34,233
What's with you? You know
that I really pack a lot.

104
00:06:34,300 --> 00:06:36,200
And I don't intend
to stay long there.

105
00:06:36,267 --> 00:06:38,667
I'll just go
because Tonito told me so.

106
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:40,367
All right.

107
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:44,200
Anyway, I already fixed
your two-day itinerary.

108
00:06:44,267 --> 00:06:46,600
As soon as you arrive
at Legazpi Domestic Airport

109
00:06:46,667 --> 00:06:49,467
the driver from car rental
services will pick you up

110
00:06:49,533 --> 00:06:51,167
so you have a service
while you are in Sorsogon.

111
00:06:52,667 --> 00:06:54,600
Just make sure
that it's a nice car.

112
00:06:54,667 --> 00:06:57,633
I don't need a driver.
I want to be totally alone.

113
00:06:57,700 --> 00:07:00,000
Noted, I'll arrange that
for you.

114
00:07:00,067 --> 00:07:03,633
Well, Dear, I hope you have
smooth skies.

115
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:04,000
And...

116
00:07:05,233 --> 00:07:06,100
enjoy.

117
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:08,933
Did you say enjoy?

118
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:36,867
Excuse me.
What is the room number

119
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:38,967
of your patient
Patricio Estrellado?

120
00:09:39,033 --> 00:09:40,333
Good morning, Ma'am.
I'll just check.

121
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:41,933
- Just wait.
- Kindly hurry.

122
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:45,067
Encarnacion, Esguerra,
Estrellado...

123
00:09:45,133 --> 00:09:46,933
Ma'am, he's already gone.

124
00:09:48,267 --> 00:09:48,533
What?

125
00:09:50,567 --> 00:09:51,933
- Yes, Ma'am. I'm sorry.
- What?

126
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,967
Mr. Estrellado is gone.

127
00:09:54,033 --> 00:09:55,233
My God...

128
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:55,767
Oh my God.

129
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:03,667
No, I wasn't able
to forgive him.

130
00:10:03,767 --> 00:10:06,500
Oh my God. Sebastian pick up,
oh my God.

131
00:10:06,567 --> 00:10:10,200
Lord, why did he die right away?
I wasn't able to talk to him.

132
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,100
I'm sorry, father.

133
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:17,367
Ma'am, excuse me.

134
00:10:17,433 --> 00:10:20,500
You thought that Mr. Estrellado
is already gone?

135
00:10:20,567 --> 00:10:21,867
No, that's not the case.

136
00:10:21,933 --> 00:10:23,867
He's gone as in he went home
already.

137
00:10:26,967 --> 00:10:27,200
What?

138
00:10:28,167 --> 00:10:29,533
Yes, he went home already.

139
00:10:36,433 --> 00:10:36,900
Thank you.

140
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,167
- Love?
 - Yes?

141
00:10:57,233 --> 00:10:59,000
Love, we have a lot of harvests
today.

142
00:11:00,133 --> 00:11:02,033
Yes, Love.

143
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:05,867
We can buy our son
a new cellphone.

144
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:07,367
That's possible.

145
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:15,800
Father, Mother,
you don't have to.

146
00:11:15,867 --> 00:11:18,567
And besides, my cellphone
is still okay.

147
00:11:18,633 --> 00:11:19,767
Really?

148
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:21,933
You should buy your needs first.

149
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:24,900
You know,

150
00:11:24,967 --> 00:11:28,667
for your father and me, we have
nothing more to ask for.

151
00:11:28,733 --> 00:11:30,633
You are enough for us.

152
00:11:34,467 --> 00:11:39,367
You are hardworking, smart,
and a loving son to the family.

153
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:40,533
Yes.

154
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:41,800
You're truly a great guy.

155
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:45,567
- That's right.
- Wait, his back is wet.

156
00:11:45,633 --> 00:11:47,167
Love, hand me the towel.

157
00:11:47,233 --> 00:11:49,067
- Thank you.
- I'll wipe it off.

158
00:11:49,133 --> 00:11:52,733
Tell me if your back is wet.

159
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,433
It's bad if you let your sweat
dry on your back.

160
00:12:04,667 --> 00:12:08,033
Mother, Father,
I think you have a visitor.

161
00:12:10,267 --> 00:12:10,933
We're not expecting anyone.

162
00:12:23,067 --> 00:12:23,633
Celeste?

163
00:12:35,167 --> 00:12:36,867
Celeste, my Child?

164
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:45,200
Sebastian, come here!

165
00:12:52,367 --> 00:12:53,500
Why didn't you tell me that
father has already been

166
00:12:53,567 --> 00:12:55,433
discharged from the hospital?

167
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:00,300
Because my charger is broken.

168
00:13:00,367 --> 00:13:01,933
Don't give me that lame excuse.

169
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:05,433
Why didn't you borrow father's
phone or your mother's?

170
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:06,867
Better yet, you're not poor.

171
00:13:06,933 --> 00:13:09,100
Why don't you buy a cellphone
or charger?

172
00:13:09,167 --> 00:13:11,100
It's just a charger.
Why didn't you text me?

173
00:13:11,167 --> 00:13:13,967
I thought you're not coming.

174
00:13:14,033 --> 00:13:15,700
Didn't you say you're busy?

175
00:13:15,767 --> 00:13:18,167
Exactly. I have so much
on my plate

176
00:13:18,233 --> 00:13:19,833
and you ruined my schedule.

177
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:22,133
Maybe you did it intentionally
so I will come here, right?

178
00:13:24,067 --> 00:13:27,067
My Child, that's enough.

179
00:13:27,133 --> 00:13:28,133
Don't argue.

180
00:13:29,467 --> 00:13:30,867
What? You're tired.

181
00:13:30,933 --> 00:13:31,633
Did you eat already?

182
00:13:33,067 --> 00:13:34,167
I'm on a water cleanse.

183
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,033
Celeste, calm down.

184
00:13:38,100 --> 00:13:39,900
I'm okay now.

185
00:13:39,967 --> 00:13:42,400
I didn't have a heart attack.

186
00:13:42,467 --> 00:13:44,967
The doctor said
it was just heartburn.

187
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:49,533
Sebastian, you know what?

188
00:13:50,533 --> 00:13:53,867
You just intentionally harassed
me, make me look haggard

189
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:56,100
so I will come here to Sorsogon.

190
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:58,433
Celeste, why are you angry?

191
00:13:58,500 --> 00:14:00,533
Aren't you happy
that Father is safe?

192
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:02,133
- That's enough.
- No, Mother.

193
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:04,067
She's getting out of hand.

194
00:14:04,133 --> 00:14:05,833
- I'm out.
- Celeste, wait.

195
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:08,067
Wait, Celeste. Stay here.

196
00:14:08,133 --> 00:14:09,933
Don't leave.

197
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,800
You know, tomorrow
there is a fiesta here.

198
00:14:12,867 --> 00:14:15,200
We will cook a lot of food.

199
00:14:15,267 --> 00:14:17,500
You should stay, Celeste.
Even for a few days.

200
00:14:18,533 --> 00:14:20,233
I can't. I'm very busy.

201
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:21,700
I need to do a lot of things.

202
00:14:21,767 --> 00:14:24,600
I will travel,
I'm getting married.

203
00:14:24,667 --> 00:14:25,200
What, Celeste?

204
00:14:26,467 --> 00:14:27,833
You're getting married?

205
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:30,567
Why didn't you tell me this?

206
00:14:30,667 --> 00:14:32,300
Who is your husband-to-be?

207
00:14:32,367 --> 00:14:34,000
Is he a good person?

208
00:14:34,067 --> 00:14:35,867
Have you known him
for a long time?

209
00:14:35,933 --> 00:14:37,133
Why do you have to know?

210
00:14:38,367 --> 00:14:41,100
Celeste, I'm your father.

211
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,033
I know you're still mad at me

212
00:14:45,633 --> 00:14:47,767
but because I'm your parent,

213
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:51,200
it's still my right to know
what's happening to you.

214
00:14:51,267 --> 00:14:53,533
You are still my responsibility.

215
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:56,433
Celeste, I'm getting older.

216
00:14:56,500 --> 00:15:00,467
You should let me be a part
of your life.

217
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:02,133
Maybe not, Father.

218
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:04,767
I'm okay.
I'm used to being alone.

219
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:07,633
Now, if you want to be a part
of my life,

220
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:10,367
you should've done that before
when my mother was still alive

221
00:15:10,433 --> 00:15:12,000
and when I was still young.

222
00:15:12,067 --> 00:15:14,100
But you chose to be a part
of someone else's life.

223
00:15:15,633 --> 00:15:22,967
My Child, I hope you get rid
of the resentment in your heart.

224
00:15:23,033 --> 00:15:24,333
You should forgive us, Celeste.

225
00:15:25,433 --> 00:15:30,833
I'm getting weak and I will
leave this Pili farm to you.

226
00:15:30,900 --> 00:15:32,333
You, Sebastian,
and your Auntie Adora

227
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:35,167
should help each other
to manage this.

228
00:15:36,867 --> 00:15:38,767
I'm not interested.

229
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:42,400
If you want to sell the farm,
if you want them to manage it,

230
00:15:42,467 --> 00:15:44,133
that's okay with me.
There's no problem

231
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:46,133
because I have my own life
in Manila.

232
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:50,200
Your own life,
it's always your own life.

233
00:15:50,267 --> 00:15:51,333
Can you not talk that way?

234
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:53,933
Let me remind you
that I'm older than you.

235
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:54,700
That's the thing, Celeste.

236
00:15:55,667 --> 00:15:58,467
You're older
but you always run away

237
00:15:58,533 --> 00:16:00,067
from your responsibilities
to the family.

238
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:04,200
You have nothing else to think
about but your frivolous work.

239
00:16:04,267 --> 00:16:05,333
Hey.

240
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:06,367
How dare you say that?

241
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:07,700
That's true.

242
00:16:09,233 --> 00:16:11,700
How do you endure ignoring
your own family?

243
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,233
It's okay. I forgive you.

244
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:17,700
You're still young.
You don't know anything yet.

245
00:16:17,767 --> 00:16:19,733
Celeste, I'm not a child
anymore.

246
00:16:21,933 --> 00:16:23,933
I know why you're being
like that.

247
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,567
Where will your anger take you?

248
00:16:26,467 --> 00:16:28,967
You don't even use
father's last name.

249
00:16:29,033 --> 00:16:31,600
Celeste, you should move on.

250
00:16:31,667 --> 00:16:32,500
You're old enough.

251
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:38,067
Oh my God, why did I come back
here to Sorsogon?

252
00:17:38,133 --> 00:17:42,367
My God, the nerve of that boy
to audaciously say that to me.

253
00:17:42,433 --> 00:17:43,867
My life is frivolous?

254
00:17:45,133 --> 00:17:47,067
To say that fashion
is frivolous.

255
00:17:47,133 --> 00:17:49,200
What kind of upbringing
did he get from them?

256
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:54,133
Well, he knows nothing
but to break pili nuts.

257
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:02,700
Hello?

258
00:19:03,733 --> 00:19:04,367
Hey, Celeste.

259
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:06,667
Book me a flight to Manila now.

260
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:09,900
I thought you'll be staying
there in Sorsogon

261
00:19:09,967 --> 00:19:11,233
for two more days.

262
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:12,800
I have no more business here.

263
00:19:12,867 --> 00:19:15,400
There's no reason for me
to stay for another day.

264
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:17,233
This isn't my home anymore.

265
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:19,567
All right, let me check.

266
00:19:19,633 --> 00:19:21,967
Tell me your preferred flight
schedule.

267
00:19:22,033 --> 00:19:23,000
The latest.

268
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:24,833
I'll just go somewhere.

269
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:26,233
All right.

270
00:20:38,433 --> 00:20:39,100
How are you, Mother?

271
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:02,200
How are you, Mother?

272
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:30,300
It's beautiful here, Mother.

273
00:21:31,333 --> 00:21:34,367
You know when your father and I
are just sweethearts,

274
00:21:34,433 --> 00:21:36,000
we often go here.

275
00:21:40,167 --> 00:21:40,967
Look at that.

276
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:48,333
Whenever you're sad,
just look at the ocean.

277
00:21:50,367 --> 00:21:54,400
Even if I'm no longer here,
it's like I'm still with you.

278
00:22:38,967 --> 00:22:43,000
I'm sorry if I just visited you
now.

279
00:22:47,733 --> 00:22:49,900
You know that when I come home
here in Sorsogon,

280
00:22:54,367 --> 00:22:56,600
all I remember...

281
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:01,467
are the bad things
that happened to our family.

282
00:23:23,533 --> 00:23:26,633
You can't compare Aurelia
and Celeste.

283
00:23:26,700 --> 00:23:29,967
And no matter what you say
about Celeste,

284
00:23:30,033 --> 00:23:31,767
that won't stop me
from marrying her.

285
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:36,200
And that will not stop me
from despising her.

286
00:23:36,267 --> 00:23:37,767
Well, I'm going out of town.

287
00:23:37,833 --> 00:23:38,967
What for?

288
00:23:39,033 --> 00:23:40,000
For my school project.

289
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:43,133
We will go to Sorsogon.

290
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:46,100
You do know that your
Auntie Celeste is there.

291
00:23:46,167 --> 00:23:47,567
Of course, I know, Dad.

292
00:23:47,633 --> 00:23:50,600
Just one look at the man
she will marry.

293
00:23:50,667 --> 00:23:53,100
He looks rich.

294
00:23:53,167 --> 00:23:57,267
He looks very successful
and very accomplished.

295
00:23:57,367 --> 00:23:59,767
Can you consider me successful?

296
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:02,100
Accomplished?

297
00:24:02,167 --> 00:24:03,633
Why did you ask that?

298
00:24:03,700 --> 00:24:08,167
I'm happy you're not discouraged
to be close to your daughter.

299
00:24:08,233 --> 00:24:11,367
I just hope that she will soften
up little by little.

300
00:24:11,433 --> 00:24:13,800
Celeste is just tough for now.

301
00:24:13,867 --> 00:24:16,100
But you can soften her heart.

302
00:24:16,167 --> 00:24:18,433
There's nothing love cannot do.

303
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:21,400
Be patient. I'll help you.

304
00:24:21,467 --> 00:24:24,967
Why did I come back here
to Sorsogon?

305
00:24:25,033 --> 00:24:28,667
Celeste!

306
00:24:28,767 --> 00:24:33,967
Next time you visit, you should
bring your boyfriend, Tonito.

307
00:24:34,033 --> 00:24:35,667
But this is the first time
I found out

308
00:24:35,733 --> 00:24:37,333
that you like guys
with almond shaped eyes.

309
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,767
Just like you.
You have almond shaped eyes.

310
00:24:38,833 --> 00:24:40,500
You look good together
in fairness

311
00:24:40,567 --> 00:24:43,633
but that's far
from Mikoy's looks.

312
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:45,367
Why, Cousin?

313
00:24:45,433 --> 00:24:47,767
How does Mikoy look like now?
